  "prompt": "Which sport can you start at the age of 26 to be a Olympian?",
  "response": "Starting a sport at the age of 26 and aiming to become an Olympian is an ambitious goal, as most athletes begin their training at a much younger age. However, there are certain sports in which it is more feasible to achieve this goal due to the nature of the skills involved and the potential for rapid improvement even later in life. Here are a few such sports:\n\n1. **Shooting:** Precision and steadiness are crucial, and physical fitness plays a role, but it is less demanding than sports requiring peak physical condition. Mental focus and technique can be developed over time.\n\n2. **Equestrian:** Success in equestrian events is heavily dependent on the relationship between the rider and the horse, skills in horse management, and riding ability. Many successful equestrians begin serious competition later in life.\n\n3. **Archery:** Similar to shooting, it relies heavily on precision, control, and mental focus. While it does require physical strength, it is possible to develop the necessary skills and techniques at a later age.\n\n4. **Curling:** This sport places a significant emphasis on strategy, precision, and teamwork. Physical fitness is important but not as critical as in other sports, allowing for success even with a later start.\n\n5. **Sailing:** Sailing requires a combination of physical skill, strategy, and experience on the water. Many sailors compete at a high level into their later years, making it feasible to start at 26 and aim for the Olympics.\n\nWhile starting at 26 poses challenges, with dedication, training, and the right approach, it is possible to achieve success in these sports at an Olympic level.",
